==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cirripedia
<hw>Cir`ri*pe"di*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>cirrus</ets> curl + <ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets>,
foot.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of Crustacea including the
barnacles. When adult, they have a calcareous shell composed of several
pieces. From the opening of the shell the animal throws out a group of
curved legs, looking like a delicate curl, whence the name of the group.
See <er>Anatifa</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cirrobranchiata</ent>⟦br⟧
